    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Not exactly what I wanted, but I found a workaround. In Eclipse 3.4 (Ganymede),  go to </p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Window->Preferences->Java->Editor->Content Assist</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>and check the checkbox for <strong>Use static imports (only 1.5 or higher)</strong>.</p>\n\n<p>This will not bring in the import on an Optimize Imports, but if you do a Quick Fix (<kbd>CTRL</kbd> + <kbd>1</kbd>) on the line it will give you the option to add the static import which is good enough.</p>\n"
